==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muscovy duck
<hw>Mus"co*vy duck`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[A corruption of
<ets>musk</ets> duck.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A duck
(<spn>Cairina moschata</spn>), larger than the common duck, often raised
in poultry yards. Called also <altname>musk duck</altname>. It is native
of tropical America, from Mexico to Southern Brazil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

